  "prompt": "Why are so many Quora users posting questions that are readily answered on Google?",
  "response": "There are several reasons why people might post easily searchable questions on Quora:\n\n1. Personal narrative: They want context-specific or personal experiences, not just factual information.\n\n2. Community interaction: They enjoy engaging with others and getting multiple perspectives.\n\n3. Perceived credibility: Some people trust answers from \"real people\" more than search results.\n\n4. Laziness: It's sometimes easier to ask than to search.\n\n5. Social validation: They want to start a conversation or get validation for their curiosity.\n\n6. Lack of search skills: Not everyone knows how to effectively use Google.\n\n7. Desire for human interpretation: They want explanations beyond basic facts.\n\nSome Quora users find this frustrating, as these low-effort questions can clutter the platform and reduce overall quality.",
